opy '%' into buf and return p still pointing to '%'.\n\nAfter get_mode returns, the code executes `switch (*p)` where p references '%'. This should trigger the case '%': branch and output a literal \"%\". However, the error occurs earlier at the `if (index > top)` check. The real issue is that we're validating argument count before determining what the format specifier actually requires—or we need to defer the argument check until we know we actually need one.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3549,"cache_read_input_tokens":52765,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3549},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38bc7cba-1d7a-4c73-805e-34ea30e20a7b","uuid":"dc4b3e91-3e16-492b-a9cc-56dc8ccfee76"}
