        be_raise(vm, \"runtime_error\", be_pushfstring(vm,\n                    \"bad argument #%d to 'format': no value\", index));\n            }\n            switch (*p) {\n            case 'd': case 'i': case 'o':\n            case 'u': case 'x': case 'X':\n                if (be_isint(vm, index)) {\n                    mode_fixlen(mode, BE_INT_FMTLEN);\n                    sprintf(buf, mode, be_toint(vm, index));\n                }\n                be_pushstring(vm, buf);\n                break;\n            case 'e': case 'E':\n            case 'f': case 'g': case 'G':\n                if (be_isnumber(vm, index)) {\n                    sprintf(buf, mode, be_toreal(vm, index));\n                }\n                be_pushstring(vm, buf);\n                break;\n            case 'c':\n                if (be_isint(vm, index)) {\n                    sprintf(buf, \"%c\", (int)be_toint(vm, index));\n                }\n                be_pushstring(vm, buf);\n                break;\n            case 's': {\n                const char *s = be_tostring(vm, index);\n                int len = be_strlen(vm, 2);\n                if (len > 100 && strlen(mode) == 2) {\n                    be_pushvalue(vm, index);\n                } else {\n                    sprintf(buf, mode, s);\n                    be_pushstring(vm, buf);\n                }\n                break;\n            }\n            default: /* error */\n                be_raise(vm, \"runtime_error\", be_pushfstring(vm,\n                    \"invalid option '%%%c' to 'format'\", *p));\n                break;\n            }\n            concat2(vm);\n            format = p + 1;\n            ++index;\n        }\n        pushstr(vm, format, strlen(format));\n        concat2(vm);\n        be_return(vm);\n    }\n    be_return_nil(vm);\n}\n\n/* string.op(s1, s2, begin=0, end=length(s2)) */\nstatic bint str_operation(bvm *vm, str_opfunc func, bint error)\n{\n    int top = be_top(vm);","numLines":75,"startLine":497,"totalLines":785}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Tz9aLuMpdJd9UzjNLTztyY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect. Now I can clearly see the bugs:\n\n**PRIMARY BUG (lines 515-518):**\nThe code checks `if (index > top)` BEFORE examining what the format specifier is (`switch (*p)` at line 519). The \"%%\" format specifier doesn't consume an argument - it just produces a single \"%\". So when we call `s.format(\"%%\")`, with no additional arguments:\n- top = 1 (only the format string)\n- index = 2 (pointing to where the first argument would be)\n- The check `if (index > top)` => `if (2 > 1)` is true, so it raises the error\n\nBut this is wrong because \"%%\" doesn't need an argument.\n\n**SECONDARY BUG (line 543):**\nIn the case 's' handler, the code does `int len = be_strlen(vm, 2);` where 2 is the position of the format string (the first argument), but it should be `int len = be_strlen(vm, index);` to get the length of the string being formatted, which is the argument at the current index position.\n\nNow let me trace through the complete flow one more time to be absolutely sure:\n\nFor `s.format(\"%%\")`:\n1. top = 1 (format string at position 1)\n2. index = 2\n3. format = \"%%\"\n4. strchr(\"%%\", '%') returns pointer to first '%'\n5. pushstr(vm, \"\", 0) and concat2(vm) - push empty string\n6. p = get_mode(pointer to second '%', mode)\n   - get_mode will parse \"%\", returning pointer to '%'\n7. buf[0] = '\\0'\n8. if (2 > 1) -> TRUE! Error raised!\n\nBut it should have proceeded to the switch statement, which would have matched case '%' and just pushed a \"%\".\n\nSo the fixes are:\n\n\nThe immediate solution is to skip the bounds check when we encounter the '%' specifier, since it doesn't require an argument. A more robust approach would be to identify the format specifier type first, then only validate argument availability for specifiers that actually need them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1954,"cache_read_input_tokens":56314,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1954},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38bc7cba-1d7a-4c73-805e-34ea30e20a7b","uuid":"318e856d-bd3b-4d61-b07a-6a4e9c7476e5"}
